# [[to]], [[at]], [[in]] or [[into]] the home, office, etc. of
#: {{uxi|fr|'''chez''' moi|at my house}}
#: {{uxi|fr|'''chez''' lui|at his house}}
#: {{uxi|fr|'''chez''' Françoise|at Françoise’s}}
#: {{uxi|fr|'''chez''' le dentiste|at the dentist}}
#: {{uxi|fr|'''chez''' l'avocat|at the lawyer's office}}
#* {{quote-text|fr|year=2013|author=Zaz|title=Je rentre
|passage=Je rentre '''chez''' vous, comme c'était '''chez''' moi, quand c'était '''chez''' nous, {{...}}
| translation=I go into where the two of you live, because it was my place, when it was our place {{...}}
|lit=I enter your place, as it was my place, (etc.)}}
# by extension, [[to]], [[at]] or [[in]] the country of
#: {{uxi|fr|une spécialité bien de '''chez''' nous|a true specialty of our country}}
#: {{uxi|fr|rentrer '''chez''' soi|to return to one's country}}
# [[in]]; [[among]] (a group of things or people of the same type)
#: {{uxi|fr|Cette maladie se voit souvent '''chez''' les chiens.|This illness is often seen '''among''' dogs.}}
#: {{uxi|fr|le TDAH '''chez''' l'adulte|ADHD '''in''' adults}}
